Something like it works for if...else...if...else too. To my horror, this was more readable and maintainable than any alternative I could imagine.<p><pre><code>    switch(override){
    default:
        printf(&quot;unexpected...\n&quot;);
        &#x2F;&#x2F; fallthrough
    case 0:
        if(z_bits&amp;4 || N_flag){
    case 100:
            handle_100();
        }else if(x_bits &amp; 0x80){
    case 200:
            handle_200();
        }else{
    case 500:
            handle_500();
        }
    }
</code></pre>
It&#x27;s cut down a bit for Hacker News. The original had about a dozen lines of code where each handle_XXX function now sits.
